  "text": "Under these conditions, the activity of the WWC reaches its maximum and sustains DpH across the thylakoid membranes [CITATION_1] . This situation is a prerequisite for the expression of the activity of CEF-PSII, because WWC does not consume ATP [CITATION_2] . Furthermore, the conditions we set up mimicked the stress imposed when photosynthesis is inhibited, allowing us to study how electrons produced in PSII are utilized under these conditions. We measured .(PSII) in intact chloroplasts to study the effect of DpH on the electron flux in PSII [",
